strategies might work best. This all seems complex, and I want to ensure I handle it correctly!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Examining method invocation tests**\\n\\nI’m looking at a test case for the `DefaultMethodInvoker` that checks if it can invoke a no-argument method. In the `InvokedTarget` class, the `greet` method is package-private, which complicates things since I need to access declared methods for native metadata. I wonder if using `getDeclaredMethod` is necessary since `MethodInvoker` makes methods accessible. It seems better to streamline by using the public `greet` method for simplicity. I'll need to ensure the correct mapping and possible updates for this process!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_PlXCKrDnk5ekeCzqybjqsL2q|fc_05de97ed4ba69501016a299a625d50819095c3aa8c8d446985", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.springframework/spring-test/7.0.0/src/test/java/org_springframework/spring_test/DefaultMethodInvokerTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage org_springframework.spring_test;\n\nimport java.lang.reflect.Method;\n\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\nimport org.springframework.test.context.MethodInvoker;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\npublic class DefaultMethodInvokerTest {\n    @Test\n    void invokesNoArgumentInstanceMethod() throws Exception {\n        InvocationTarget target = new InvocationTarget();\n        Method method = InvocationTarget.class.getMethod(\"greeting\");\n\n        Object result = MethodInvoker.DEFAULT_INVOKER.invoke(method, target);\n\n        assertThat(result).isEqualTo(\"hello from default invoker\");\n        assertThat(target.isInvoked()).isTrue();\n    }\n\n    public static class InvocationTarget {\n        private boolean invoked;\n\n        public String greeting() {\n            this.invoked = true;\n            return \"hello from default invoker\";\n        }\n\n        boolean isInvoked() {\n            return this.invoked;\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}, "partialJson": "{\"path\":\"tests/src/org.springframework/spring-test/7.0.0/src/test/java/org_springframework/spring_test/DefaultMethodInvokerTest.java\",\"content\":\"/*\\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\\n *\\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\\n */\\npackage org_springframework.spring_test;\\n\\nimport java.lang.reflect.Method;\\n\\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\\n\\nimport org.springframework.test.context.MethodInvoker;\\n\\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\\n\\npublic class DefaultMethodInvokerTest {\\n    @Test\\n    void invokesNoArgumentInstanceMethod() throws Exception {\\n        InvocationTarget target = new InvocationTarget();\\n        Method method = InvocationTarget.class.getMethod(\\\"greeting\\\");\\n\\n        Object result = MethodInvoker.DEFAULT_INVOKER.invoke(method, target);\\n\\n        assertThat(result).isEqualTo(\\\"hello from default invoker\\\");\\n        assertThat(target.isInvoked()).isTrue();\\n    }\\n\\n    public static class InvocationTarget {\\n        private boolean invoked;\\n\\n        public String greeting() {\\n            this.invoked = true;\\n            return \\\"hello from default invoker\\\";\\n        }\\n\\n        boolean isInvoked() {\\n            return this.invoked;\\n        }\\n    }\\n}\\n\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1102, "output": 790, "cacheRead": 18944, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 20836, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1781111379117, "responseId": "resp_05de97ed4ba69501016a299a53e6a88